    "content": "nullRevenue Lifecycle Management\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Revenue Lifecycle Management\n Get Started with Revenue Lifecycle Management\n Revenue Lifecycle Management Billable Usage Types\n Upgrade Revenue Lifecycle Management to the Latest Release\n Product Catalog Management\n Salesforce Pricing\n Product Configurator\n Learn and Explore Product Configurator\n Enable Product Configurator\n Explore the Product Configurator Flow\n Work With the Product Configurator\n Configuration Rules\n Set Up Configuration Rules\n Create a Rule Library\n Activate a Rule Library Version\n Turn On Configuration Rules\n Create a Configuration Rule\n Edit a Configuration Rule\n Delete a Configuration Rule\n Third-Party Configurator\n Quote and Order Capture and Asset Lifecycle\n Dynamic Revenue Orchestrator\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nREVENUE LIFECYCLE MANAGEMENT\nConfiguration Rules\n\nWhen you configure products for sale, ensure that all your products have valid attributes and are compatible with other products in the offering. With configuration rules in Product Catalog Management, you can ensure that your users select the right set of products and that the product configuration aligns with the business needs and standards.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Developer, Enterprise, and Unlimited Editions where Revenue Lifecycle Management and Product Configurator are enabled.\n\nConfiguration rules streamline the product configuration experience and reduce configuration errors. You eliminate fallout due to faulty product configurations when you use the validation, exclusion, and require rules. A perfect product configuration ensures accurate quotes and orders, and a smooth customer experience.\n\nProduct Configurator supports the different action types based on the condition criteria.\n\nAction Types\nACTION TYPE\tDESCRIPTION\tEXAMPLE\nValidate\tValidate whether a product and its attributes are correctly configured by providing the user a message.\tIf the user selects a laptop of brand A as part of a laptop bundle, then the docking station must be brand X, and the headphones must be brand Y. If the bundled product doesn’t meet these criteria, then the user sees a validation error message.\nExclude\tExclude a product along with its attributes by providing the user a message.\tThe user mustn’t select phone chargers of type X when they select phones of make Y in a bundle.\nRequire\tInclude a product along with its attributes by providing the user a message.\tThe user must select a specific ink cartridge when they select a specific printer as part of the printer bundle.\nAuto-Add\tAutomatically add a product to the bundle when the rule executes.\tIf the user adds 5 laptops and is a gold status customer, then automatically add a keyboard.\nAuto-Remove\tAutomatically remove a product from the bundle when the rule executes.\tIf the user selects Refurbished as the type for a laptop, then automatically remove the 1-year warranty.\nSet Attribute\tSet one or more attributes of a product to the appropriate value.\tIf the user selects a laptop with advanced as configuration type, then set the value of the power adapter to 96 W.\nSet Quantity\tSet the quantity of a product to a certain numerical value.\tIf the user selects a limited edition laptop, then automatically set the quantity of the product to 1.\n\nWhen you set up configuration rules, you also define the messages that your agents or sales reps see when the rule executes. Your agents or sales reps can use the messages to rectify the product configuration and significantly reduce the product’s time to market.\n\nSet Up Configuration Rules\nDefine and invoke configuration rules when configuring products.\nCreate a Rule Library\nRule creation requires a rule library. This library stores and runs the rules in the engine\nActivate a Rule Library Version\nUse the rule library version to store and run rules in the rule engine.\nTurn On Configuration Rules\nGrant users access to configuration rules.\nCreate a Configuration Rule\nReduce configuration errors and easily manage product validation and compatibility using configuration rules.\nEdit a Configuration Rule\nTo add, update, or delete rule conditions and actions, modify the rule details or the rule criteria.\nDelete a Configuration Rule\nDelete a configuration rule when you no longer need it.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
